      • createChannel

        public TGChannel createChannel(java.lang.String urlPath,
                               java.lang.String userName,
                               java.lang.String password)
                        throws TGException
        Description copied from class: TGChannelFactory
        Create a channel on the URL specified using the userName and password. A URL is represented as a string of the form ://[user@]['['ipv6']'] | ipv4 [:][port][/]'{' name:value;... '}'
        Specified by:
        createChannel in class TGChannelFactory
        Parameters:
        urlPath - A url string.
        userName - The userName for the channel. The userId provided overrides all other userIds that can be infered. The rules for overriding are in this order a. The argument 'userId' is the highest priority. If Null then b. The user@url is considered. If that is Null c. the "userID=value" from the URL string is considered. d. If all of them is Null, then the default User associated to the installation will be taken.
        password - An encrypted password associated with the userName
        Returns:
        a Channel
        Throws:
        TGException
        See Also:
        for detailed URL specification

        public TGChannel createChannel(java.lang.String urlPath,
                               java.lang.String userName,
                               java.lang.String password,
                               java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> props)
                        throws TGException
        Description copied from class: TGChannelFactory
        Create a channel on the URL specified using the user Name and password
        Specified by:
        createChannel in class TGChannelFactory
        Parameters:
        urlPath - A url as a string form
        userName - The userName for the channel. The userId provided overrides all other userIds that can be infered. The rules for overriding are in this order a. The argument 'userId' is the highest priority. If Null then b. The user@url is considered. If that is Null c. the "userID=value" from the URL string is considered. d. The user retrieved from the Properties is considered e. If all of them is Null, then the default User associated to the installation will be taken.
        password - Encrypted password
        props - A properties bag with Connection Properties. The URL infered properties override this property bag.
        Returns:
        a connected channel
        Throws:
        TGException
